As we mentioned in our recent email messages, we are removing the option to use PHP 7.3 from our platform.

On October 12th, we will begin automatically switching sites using PHP 7.3 to PHP 7.4.

Make sure your site is ready for the change

We strongly recommend switching your sites to PHP 7.4 yourself before the automatic change on October 12th. That way, you can check to ensure that going from PHP 7.3 to 7.4 will not break anything on your site.

While it's unlikely that the move from PHP 7.3 to 7.4 will have a negative effect, it's still best practice to test your site and plugins to be sure. You can test the changes in a staging environment and update your live site when you're satisfied that your site is working properly with the new PHP version.

Unsupported versions of PHP are a security risk

Security vulnerabilities discovered in unsupported PHP versions cannot be fixed, that's why Kinsta removes the option to use unsupported versions.

If you want to read about some of the benefits and changes in recent PHP versions, check out our articles, What's New in PHP 7.4 and What's New in PHP 8.

How to upgrade to the latest version of PHP

Upgrading PHP versions in MyKinsta is as easy as selecting a new version from a dropdown menu. Our safe PHP upgrades guide provides step-by-step instructions.

Be aware that switching versions may break your site. We suggest using a staging environment to test the switch. That way, your live site will not be affected until you're ready to push staging to the live site.

If your site breaks after upgrading to the latest version of PHP

Make sure the code on your site does not use any functions no longer supported by recent versions of PHP. Check your plugins and the active theme. The safe PHP upgrades guide mentioned above can help you troubleshoot some of the more common upgrade issues.

We know that technology updates can be inconvenient and disruptive. But Kinsta is dedicated to providing you with the best, most secure website hosting environment anywhere. To be truly secure, your sites should always use the safest, most up-to-date technology available.

If you have any questions about the PHP version changes, we're here for you. Feel free to connect with us in MyKinsta.
The Kinsta Team
